{"id":"quant-ph/0504123","submitter":"Stephan I. Tzenov","authors":"Stephan I. Tzenov","title":"Irrotational Momentum Fluctuations Conditioning the Quantum Nature of\n  Physical Processes","comments":"8 pages, no figures","journal-ref":null,"doi":"10.1142/S0217751X06033866","report-no":null,"categories":"quant-ph nlin.PS","license":null,"abstract":"  Starting from a simple classical framework and employing some stochastic\nconcepts, the basic ingredients of the quantum formalism are recovered. It has\nbeen shown that the traditional axiomatic structure of quantum mechanics can be\nrebuilt, so that the quantum mechanical framework resembles to a large extent\nthat of the classical statistical mechanics. The main assumption used here is\nthe existence of a random irrotational component in the classical momentum.\nVarious basic elements of the quantum formalism (calculation of expectation\nvalues, the Heisenberg uncertainty principle, the correspondence principle) are\nrecovered by applying traditional techniques, borrowed from classical\nstatistical mechanics.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Sat, 16 Apr 2005 12:03:42 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sun, 23 Oct 2005 06:51:49 GMT"}],"update_date":"2009-11-11"}
